If I am missing some information, please let me know.  In fact, it would appear that they have more innate ability to deal damage then a warrior, but I am giving warriors the benefit of the doubt that some other table and/or innate crit abilities make up the difference. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirlageholyblaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Lage Holyblaze</A> at: 4/11/02 9:33:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 1845<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/11/02 9:39:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15242.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why TO petition: PoP</span><hr size=1> Pushing Sup Heal down a few levels would be nice, its brutal for me healing 2600-2700hp unbuffed with gheal.  Maybe lowering the reuse on Holyforge /shrug<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> 4. Our silence spell was nerfed right into the ground. The spell now costs me more mana, stuns for less time, and has a longer recast time than stuns that I already have. We were told that it was nerfed and they would be fixing it or changing it. This has been 4 months now.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
